-- World Diamond Council May Allow Supervised Zimbabwe Marange Gem Exports
-- B y   A n t o n y   S g u a z z i n
-- 2011-02-03T17:14:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-03/world-diamond-council-may-allow-supervised-zimbabwe-marange-gem-exports.html
The World Diamond Council said it has
agreed to allow  Zimbabwe  to export gems from the Marange field
if the country agrees to “oversight and monitoring.”  Talks between Zimbabwe and Mathieu Yamba, the chairman of
the Kimbereley Process, are being held to see if agreement can
be reached, the council said in an e-mailed statement today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  